    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Before you start cooking, take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Rinse your<strong> brown rice</strong>, add it to a pot with plenty of <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 20-25 min or until it's tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain, return it to the pot and keep covered until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-gochujang-double-chicken-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> chicken breast strips </strong>and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until lightly golden</p><p>(Doubled your protein? Use 2 pans!)</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-gochujang-double-chicken-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-gochujang-double-chicken-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once lightly golden, add your <strong>sweet pea pods </strong>to the pan with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Cook for 3-4 min or until slightly softened</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-gochujang-double-chicken-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add your <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>gochujang paste</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!), <strong>tomato paste </strong>and <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame oil</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>brown sugar</strong></p><p>Add 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[200ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and mix it all together \u2013 this is your <strong>spicy gochujang sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-gochujang-double-chicken-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sweet pea pods are slightly softened, add 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and give everything a good mix up until nicely coated</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-gochujang-double-chicken-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once nicely coated, add the <strong>spicy gochujang sauce </strong>and your <strong>shredded veg mix </strong>to the pan and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for a final 4-5 or until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>gochujang chicken stir fry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/spicy-gochujang-double-chicken-stir-fry-with-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>spicy</strong> <strong>gochujang XL chicken stir fry</strong> over the <strong>cooked rice</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
